{"id":2293,"date":"2022-06-18T21:55:13","date_gmt":"2022-06-18T21:55:13","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/robotics.gabysoft.com\/?page_id=2293"},"modified":"2024-09-02T19:01:36","modified_gmt":"2024-09-02T19:01:36","slug":"wiring-test","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wiring-test\/","title":{"rendered":"Wiring Tests"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Now that we have it wired, we need to run a few tests to see if it is wired correctly.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The first thing you want to do when you turn the power on is to check to see if all of the devices are getting power by looking at their power indicator lights. The devices are the <strong>Raspberry Pi<\/strong>, 3 <strong>Motor Controllers<\/strong>, the <strong>Microcontroller<\/strong>, the <strong>Shooter Motor<\/strong>, the <strong>Turntable Motor<\/strong>, and the <strong>Gyro<\/strong>. Note that the <strong>Drive Motors<\/strong> and the <strong>Feeder Motor<\/strong> do not have lights.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"512\" height=\"474\" data-id=\"2308\"  src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/PiPower.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2308\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/PiPower.jpg 512w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/PiPower-300x278.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/PiPower-150x139.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" \/><figcaption>Raspberry Pi<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"512\" height=\"494\" data-id=\"2304\"  src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/MotorControllerPower.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2304\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/MotorControllerPower.jpg 512w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/MotorControllerPower-300x289.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/MotorControllerPower-150x145.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" \/><figcaption>Motor Controller x3<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"512\" height=\"472\" data-id=\"2305\"  src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/MicroControllerPower.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2305\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/MicroControllerPower.jpg 512w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/MicroControllerPower-300x277.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/MicroControllerPower-150x138.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" \/><figcaption>Microcontroller<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"512\" height=\"495\" data-id=\"2309\"  src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/ShooterMotorPower.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2309\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/ShooterMotorPower.jpg 512w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/ShooterMotorPower-300x290.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/ShooterMotorPower-150x145.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" \/><figcaption>Shooter Motor<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"512\" height=\"486\" data-id=\"2306\"  src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/TurntableMotorPower.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2306\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/TurntableMotorPower.jpg 512w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/TurntableMotorPower-300x285.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/TurntableMotorPower-150x142.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" \/><figcaption>Turntable Motor<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"512\" height=\"486\" data-id=\"2307\"  src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/GyroPower.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2307\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/GyroPower.jpg 512w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/GyroPower-300x285.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/GyroPower-150x142.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" \/><figcaption>Gyro<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If <strong>ANY<\/strong> of these lights are <strong>not <\/strong>on, you should turn the robot off immediately and check the power connections.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, in <strong>VS Code<\/strong>, open the folder <strong>NerfBotWiringTest<\/strong> and run that program on your <strong>NerfBot<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Test Drive Motors<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Pressing <strong>Button 1<\/strong> on the joystick should cause the <strong>Left Motor<\/strong> to run for two seconds followed by the <strong>Right Motor<\/strong> running for two seconds. The speeds of the left and right motors are logged to the <strong>TERMINAL <\/strong>window. You should verify that the left motor is the one that is running during the first two second and the right motor is running during the second 2 seconds. Also monitor the <strong>TERMINAL <\/strong>output to verify the the encoders for the left and right motors are working.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Test Shooter Motor<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Press and hold <strong>Button 2<\/strong> and the <strong>Shooter Motor<\/strong> should run. The speed should also be displayed in the <strong>TERMINAL<\/strong> window.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Test Feeder Motor<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Press and hold <strong>Button 3<\/strong> and the <strong>Feeder Motor<\/strong> should run. The speed should also be displayed in the <strong>TERMINAL<\/strong> window.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Test Turntable Motor<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Press and hold <strong>Button 4<\/strong> and the Turntable Motor should run. The speed should also be displayed in the <strong>TERMINAL <\/strong>window.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Test Limit Switches<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Pressing <strong>Button 5<\/strong> will start displaying the state of the left and right limit switches in the <strong>TERMINAL <\/strong>window. While this command is running activate both the left and right switches to see that their state is properly reported. Pressing <strong>Button 5<\/strong> a second time will stop the test.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Test Camera Light<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Press and hold <strong>Button 6<\/strong> and the <strong>Camera Light<\/strong> should come on.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Test the Ball Counter<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Pressing <strong>Button 7<\/strong> will start displaying the ball count in the <strong>TERMINAL <\/strong>window. Use your finger to break the beam sensor and verify that the count increases.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Test the Navigator<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Pressing <strong>Button 8<\/strong> should start the <strong>Navigator<\/strong>. The <strong>Navigator <\/strong>will first initialize which will take a few seconds. When the initialization is complete it should display the current <strong>Yaw <\/strong>in the <strong>TERMINAL <\/strong>window. Rotate the robot and verify that the <strong>Gyro <\/strong>is working.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Now that we have it wired, we need to run a few tests to see if it is wired correctly. The first thing you want to do when you turn the power on is to check to see if all of the devices are getting power by looking at their power indicator lights. The devices&hellip;&nbsp;<a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wiring-test\/\" class=\"\" rel=\"bookmark\">Read More &raquo;<span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Wiring Tests<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","template":"","meta":{"neve_meta_sidebar":"","neve_meta_container":"","neve_meta_enable_content_w